narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: the notion of freedom, in the context of tons to different political, philosophical and sociological texts. fascinating.

This seminar presents a survey of different philosophical frameworks relating to the concept of freedom. The readings can be very dense, but once you get through them, applying the philosophies can lead to very interesting and enlightening discussions.
YES! TAKE. THIS. SEMINAR. APPLY FOR IT AND MAKE SURE YOU'RE IN!
Take it if you want to learn about different intellectual perspectives on freedom. If you're sure that you want to learn about it, then this class will do a great job of fulfilling your expectations.
THE WORST CLASS EVER! AVOID TAKING IT AT ALL COSTS!!!
Yes, even though the grading was sometimes difficult, the reading is all really interesting (and usually manageable) and Prof. Landemore is nice and interesting.
